\u201cO Gabriel, what is this?\u201d Gabriel said, \u201cI do not know until I ask the All-Knowing.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34760,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/23\/dhikr-angels-announce\/","url_meta":{"origin":37906,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Dhikr: Angels declare forgiveness for circles of remembrance","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 23, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Sahl ibn Hanzalah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo people sit together to remember Allah Almighty and stand to leave until a heavenly caller says to them: Stand and your sins are forgiven by Allah! Your bad deeds have been replaced with good\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":41747,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/01\/17\/expiation-illness\/","url_meta":{"origin":37906,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Sickness: Expiation of sins for enduring illness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 17, 2024","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, when the Muslim falls ill, Allah Almighty inspires the angels, saying: O angels, I have detained My servant with My confinement. If I take his soul, he will be forgiven. If I heal his body,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0